In[36]:
sns.set_theme(style='darkgrid')
plt.figure(figsize=(12,5))
ax = sns.countplot(data=present_students, x='Category', palette='pastel')
ax.set_title('No. of Students Vs Category')
ax.set_ylabel('Number of Students')
plt.xticks(rotation=0)

# annotate counts on top of bars
for p in ax.patches:
    ax.annotate(int(p.get_height()), (p.get_x()+p.get_width()/2., p.get_height()),
                ha='center', va='bottom')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

sns.set_theme(style="darkgrid")
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 7))

# Convert Percentage column to float
data = present_students['Percentage (%)'].str.replace('%', '').astype(float)

# Define bins and labels
bins = np.arange(0, 101, 10)  # 0,10,20,...,100
labels = [f'{i+1}-{i+10}' for i in range(0, 100, 10)]

# Bin the data
present_students['Percentage Bin'] = pd.cut(
    data, bins=bins, labels=labels, right=True, include_lowest=True
)

# Count per bin
counts = present_students['Percentage Bin'].value_counts().sort_index()

# Create colors
colors = sns.color_palette("viridis", len(counts))

# Plot bars
for i, (label, count) in enumerate(counts.items()):
    plt.bar(label, count, color=colors[i], edgecolor='black')
    
    # Annotate count
    plt.text(i, count + 0.5, str(count), ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=10, weight='bold')
    
    # Annotate percentage
    pct = f'{count / len(data) * 100:.1f}%'
    plt.text(i, count + 3, pct, ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=10, color='darkblue', weight='bold')

plt.title("Distribution of Overall Student Percentages", fontsize=18, weight='bold')
plt.xlabel("Percentage Range")
plt.ylabel("Number of Students")
plt.xticks(rotation=0)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
